            "description": "The request was processed successfully. A stream of updates will be returned to the client as they\nbecome available. Each update is separated by a CRLF pair, so a section of data followed by a\nCR-LF-CR-LF sequence is one update. Each update is a JSON object, as below.\n",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "url": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "description": "The URL that caused this chunk of data to be sent",
                      "example": "/v1/timer/video_countdown"
                    },
                    "data": {
                      "type": {},
                      "description": "The data object that was returned by the given URL. This is in the same data format\nas the given URL returns natively.\n",
